race.comment: SAFARI BOY (2) is still a maiden after 14 starts but looks well placed in this race on the back of a disappointing effort at Belmont last time out. Back to a race of this calibre looks ideal and if he gets some luck from the barrier, he'll be very hard to hold out. CANTILEVER (1) should be peaking now after finishing second over 1410m at this track last time at the third run of the campaign. Well placed and should go well again. BEST RESULT (7) is building nicely this campaign and now strikes this third-up for the in-form apprentice. Rates well in this field and can put her best foot forward. PROVE ME WRONG (6) is racing in good order and is not to be discounted.
